<%- content_for :title, "Koi Styleguide: Tables" -%>

<%- content_for :side do -%>
  <%= render "sidebar" -%>
<%- end -%>

<div class="spacing">

  <p>By default, tables are mostly unstyled:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Table Heading</th>
        <th>Table Heading</th>
        <th>Table Heading</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Table cell</td>
        <td>Table cell</td>
        <td>Table cell</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Table cell</td>
        <td>Table cell</td>
        <td>Table cell</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>You can apply the generic koi table styles by adding the class "table".</p>
  <p>Make sure you always wrap your tables in a div with the class of <code>table-container</code> to ensure it can be scrolled when the screen is too small.</p>

  <div class="table-contaner">
    <table class="table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Table Heading</th>
          <th>Table Heading</th>
          <th>Table Heading</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Table cell</td>
          <td>Table cell</td>
          <td>Table cell</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Table cell</td>
          <td>Table cell</td>
          <td>Table cell</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p>You can apply left-hand heading styles by giving the <code>th</code>s the <code>table-col-heading</code> class.

  <div class="table-contaner">
    <table class="table">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th class="table-col-heading">Table cell</th>
          <td>Table cell</td>
          <td>Table cell</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th class="table-col-heading">Table cell</th>
          <td>Table cell</td>
          <td>Table cell</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>


</div>